# Vercel Web Analytics Integration

Successfully implemented Vercel Web Analytics for the StudyNotion React application.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed Dependencies
- Installed `@vercel/analytics@^1.6.1` package using npm with --legacy-peer-deps flag (required due to peer dependency conflicts with existing TypeScript version)

### 2. Modified Files

#### frontend/src/App.js
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/react";`
- Added `<Analytics />` component to the JSX, placed after `<Navbar />` component
- The Analytics component will track page views and user interactions across the entire application

#### frontend/package.json
- Added "@vercel/analytics": "^1.6.1" to dependencies

#### frontend/package-lock.json
- Updated with new dependencies for @vercel/analytics package

## Implementation Details

The Analytics component is placed in the main App.js file within the root div element. This ensures that:
- Analytics tracking is active across all routes and pages
- The component is rendered once at the application level
- All page navigation events will be automatically tracked

## Verification Steps Completed

✅ Package installed successfully
✅ Build completed successfully (no errors)
✅ ESLint validation passed (via build process)
✅ Lock files updated properly
✅ Existing code structure preserved

## Notes

- The Analytics component from `@vercel/analytics/react` is specifically designed for plain React applications
- It will automatically track page views and interactions without requiring additional configuration
- Analytics data will be visible in the Vercel dashboard once the application is deployed to Vercel
- No environment variables or additional configuration is required for basic functionality
